description:
Story #1 - Christmas list - Archie and Jughead head to the woods to cut a yule log for Christmas.

Story #2 - Hide and Peek - Li'l Jinx searches for the Christmas presents she know's her parents have hidden in the house.

Story #3 - Foot Steps - Archie annoys Mr. Lodge by stomping around in the new boot's he got for Christmas and causing him to break an expensive vase.

Story #4 - Yule Chuckles - Three, two panel stories starring Archie, Veronica and Moose.

Story #5 - The Spirit Is Willing - Mr. Weatherbee tries to instill the spirit of giving into Archie and the gang after he overhears them talking about how much they like getting a lot of presents for Christmas.

Story #6 - Arty Party - During Veronica's Christmas party Archie and the other guest's here carolers outside and once they see the carolers are children from the local orphanage they decide to give their own presents to the children.
name: Archie's Christmas Stocking

description: The first issue of Cassandra Clare's New York Times best-selling novel, The Mortal Instruments: City of Bones, a young adult fantasy series in which a young teen girl discovers a shadowy world filled with demon-hunting warriors. When fifteen-year-old Clary Fray heads out to the Pandemonium Club in New York City, she hardly expects to witness a murder-- much less a murder committed by three teenagers with strange tattoos and brandishing strange weapons. So begins Clary's initial journey into the world of Shadowhunters: a secret tribe dedicated to ridding the earth of demons. A tribe, that until now, had remained secret to all ordinary mundanes... Th3rd World Studios is proud to present the first chapter in their adaptation of Cassandra Clare's New York Times Bestseller and upcoming major motion picture release, The Mortal Instruments: City of Bones. (Also features a FREE preview of Th3rd World Studios' New York Times bestselling graphic novel, The Stuff of Legend)
name: Dark Descent
